<article title='Antacid'><paragraph><link><target>Image:Antacid-L478.jpg</target><part>thumb</part><part>Antacid tablets</part></link>An<space/><bold>antacid</bold><space/>is a substance which<space/><link><target>neutralization (chemistry)</target><part>neutralizes</part></link><space/><link><target>gastric acid</target><part>stomach acidity</part></link>, which in turn relieves<space/><link><target>heartburn</target></link>.</paragraph><heading level='2'>Medical uses</heading><paragraph><link><target>Image:Old aluminum tablets.JPG</target><part>200px</part><part>thumb</part><part>Wyeth amphojel tablets of aluminum hydroxide.</part></link>Antacids are available<space/><link><target>over the counter</target></link><space/>and are taken by mouth to quickly relieve occasional<space/><link><target>heartburn</target></link>, the major symptom of<space/><link><target>gastroesophageal reflux disease</target></link>. Treatment with antacids alone is symptomatic and only justified for minor symptoms.<extension extension_name='ref' name="AHRQ">U.S. Department of Health &amp; Human Services. Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality 23 September 2011<space/><link type='external' href='http://effectivehealthcare.ahrq.gov/index.cfm/search-for-guides-reviews-and-reports/?pageaction=displayproduct&amp;amp;productID=756'>Consumer Summary - Treatment Options for GERD or Acid Reflux Disease: A Review of the Research for Adults</link></extension></paragraph><paragraph>Antacids are distinct from acid-reducing drugs like<space/><link><target>H2-receptor antagonist</target><trail>s</trail></link><space/>or<space/><link><target>proton pump inhibitor</target><trail>s</trail></link><space/>and they do not kill the bacteria,<space/><italics><link><target>Helicobacter pylori</target></link></italics>, which causes most<space/><link><target>gastric ulcer</target><part>ulcers</part></link>.<extension extension_name='ref' name="AHRQ"></extension></paragraph><heading level='2'>Side effects</heading><paragraph>Versions with magnesium may cause diarrhea, and brands with calcium or aluminium may cause constipation and rarely, long-term use may cause kidney stones. Long term use of versions with aluminum may increase the risk for getting<space/><link><target>osteoporosis</target></link>.<extension extension_name='ref' name="MedlinePlus">U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, National Institutes of Health, U.S. National Library of Medicine. Page last updated: 07 November 2014<space/><link type='external' href='http://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/ency/patientinstructions/000198.htm'>Medline Plus: Taking Antacids</link></extension></paragraph><heading level='2'>Mechanism of action</heading><paragraph>Antacids contain<space/><link><target>alkaline</target></link><space/>ions that directly<space/><link><target>Neutralization (chemistry)</target><part>neutralize</part></link><space/>stomach<space/><link><target>gastric acid</target></link>.<extension extension_name='ref' name="Overview"><template><target>cite journal</target><arg name="last1">Zajac</arg><arg name="first1">P</arg><arg name="last2">Holbrook</arg><arg name="first2">A</arg><arg name="last3">Super</arg><arg name="first3">ME</arg><arg name="last4">Vogt</arg><arg name="first4">M<space/></arg><arg name="title">An overview: Current clinical guidelines for the evaluation, diagnosis, treatment, and management of dyspepsia</arg><arg name="journal">Osteopathic Family Physician<space/></arg><arg name="volume">5<space/></arg><arg name="issue">2<space/></arg><arg name="pages">79–85<space/></arg><arg name="date">March–April 2013<space/></arg><arg name="pmid"></arg><arg name="doi">10.1016/j.osfp.2012.10.005</arg></template></extension></paragraph><heading level='2'>Some well-known antacid brands</heading><paragraph>Antacids are generally a<space/><link><target>salt (chemistry)</target><part>chemical salt</part></link><space/>of an<space/><link><target>alkaline</target></link><space/>ion and a<space/><link><target>counterion</target></link>, as shown in the table below. The alkaline ion is generally<space/><link><target>bicarbonate</target></link><space/>but may also be<space/><link><target>hydroxide</target></link>.</paragraph><table class="wikitable sortable"><tablerow><tablehead>Product</tablehead><tablehead>Alkaline ion</tablehead><tablehead><link><target>Al(OH)3</target><part>Aluminium</part></link></tablehead><tablehead><link><target>CaCO3</target><part>Calcium</part></link></tablehead><tablehead><link><target>Mg(OH)2</target><part>Magnesium</part></link></tablehead><tablehead><link><target>KHCO3</target><part>Potassium</part></link></tablehead><tablehead><link><target>NaHCO3</target><part>Sodium</part></link></tablehead></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell><link><target>Alka-Seltzer</target></link></tablecell><tablecell>bicarbonate</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell>Andrews Antacid</tablecell><tablecell>bicarbonate</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell><link><target>Brioschi (company)</target><part>Brioschi</part></link></tablecell><tablecell>bicarbonate</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell><link><target>List of Wal-Mart brands#Equate</target><part>Equate</part></link></tablecell><tablecell>bicarbonate</tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell><link><target>Maalox</target></link><space/>(liquid)</tablecell><tablecell>bicarbonate</tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell>X</tablecell><tablecell></tablecell><tablecell></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell>Maalox